## FINAL PROVISIONS

### Article 11 ‚Äì Entry into Force

1. This Convention enters into force 90 days after the 30th ratification.
1. For subsequent ratifying states, entry into force occurs 30 days post-ratification.

### Article 12 ‚Äì Amendments

1. Amendments may be proposed by any State Party or UN-AIOEA.
1. Amendments require two-thirds majority of States Parties.
1. Technical annexes may be updated by UN-AIOEA with 60-day notice.

### Article 13 ‚Äì Reservations

Reservations incompatible with the object and purpose of this Convention are prohibited.

### Article 14 ‚Äì Withdrawal

1. Withdrawal requires 12-month notice.
1. Existing AI certifications remain valid for 24 months post-withdrawal.
1. MLA obligations continue for ongoing investigations.

